\textcolor{blue}{\textbf{Checkpoint Idea:} For each of the following logarithmic expressions, identify which logarithm law, if any, can be applied
\begin{itemize}
    \item Give a variety of examples here, where some of them can't be simplified using the logarithm laws, like $\ln (x+3)$
\end{itemize}}

\textcolor{blue}{\textbf{Checkpoint Idea:} Re-write each of the following logarithmic expressions as a single logarithm
\begin{itemize}
    \item $2\ln 8 - 5 \ln 2$
    \item $\ln 12 + \ln 2 - \ln 6$
    \item $2\ln 8 + \ln 9 - \ln 36$
    \item $5\ln (x-2) - \ln (x+5)+3\ln x$
\end{itemize}}

  </p>
